{"id":14880966,"mediaExerciseId":"2a22f267-b55f-4db6-9d04-4d54180a3ee3","exerciseName":"28","chapterName":"6","chapterTitle":"Discounted Cash Flow Valuation","groupId":612301,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":186,"solutions":[{"id":6001736,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we will calculate the present value of the cash flows using the appropriate discount rate of 7.17%. \n\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"First, let's identify what the present value is.\n\nThe present value annuity determines the current value of a specific future amount. It is calculated by considering the future payments from an annuity and following a specified discount rate.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Next, determine how the present value is calculated.\n\nThe present value can be calculated using the following equation:\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Present Value} &=\\dfrac{{FV}_{t}}{\\left(1 + r\\right)^{t}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWhere:\n\n$FV$, which refers to the cash flow\\\n$t$, which represent the period\\\n$r$, which indicate the discount rate","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/520aa5d763be67745727d94dcad39e2b/fed40bcee71308ad9c7b0e20e9202b10/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/520aa5d763be67745727d94dcad39e2b/fed40bcee71308ad9c7b0e20e9202b10/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Utilizing the present value function, we will calculate the present value of each cash flow yearly using the discounted rate and combine the values to determine the net present value of the cashflows.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/520aa5d763be67745727d94dcad39e2b/0b96b128111a6f5a831e13802b201732/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/520aa5d763be67745727d94dcad39e2b/0b96b128111a6f5a831e13802b201732/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"We will consider the following details inc calculating the present value.\n\n- The discount rate of 7.17%\n\nWe must consider the cash flows given in the exercise. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":334,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/520aa5d763be67745727d94dcad39e2b/17272ab6cd62c325d1691471aed5bf83/lateximg_large.png","width":865},"regular":{"height":168,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/520aa5d763be67745727d94dcad39e2b/17272ab6cd62c325d1691471aed5bf83/lateximg.png","width":432}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's now determine the present value of the cash flows.\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{PV} &=\\dfrac{\\$2,480}{\\left(1 + 0.0717\\right)^{1}}+\\dfrac{\\$0}{\\left(1 + 0.0717\\right)^{2}}+\\dfrac{\\$3,920}{\\left(1 + 0.0717\\right)^{3}}+\\dfrac{\\$2,170}{\\left(1 + 0.0717\\right)^{4}}\n\\\\[10pt]\n&=\\$ 2,314.08  +\\$ 0+\\$ 3,184.68 +\\$ 1,645.00 \n\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\boxed{\\bf\\$ 7,143.77}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n**Hence, the present value of the cash flows is $7,143.77.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/520aa5d763be67745727d94dcad39e2b/03bfb287e1ec86cf57083e66aa1a9f23/lateximg_large.png","width":998},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/520aa5d763be67745727d94dcad39e2b/03bfb287e1ec86cf57083e66aa1a9f23/lateximg.png","width":500}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"To deduce, we determined the present value of the multiple cash flows by calculating the present value each year and combining the values. Hence, our calculation result is $7,143.77.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"f0cb13a8-4d92-4035-9402-2518af5b7bca","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":7}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880967,"exerciseName":"29","page":186,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"4536050a-c270-4e23-a816-818c7ac2eddc","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-questions-and-problems-29-4536050a-c270-4e23-a816-818c7ac2eddc"},{"id":14880968,"exerciseName":"30","page":186,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"e83d193f-425e-46c8-819e-0fd921d64d10","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-questions-and-problems-30-e83d193f-425e-46c8-819e-0fd921d64d10"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880965,"exerciseNam